Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces, and pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Rub the oil over the potatoes then spread out on the baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until fork tender, ~{25-35%minutes}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Irish pork mince{240%g}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, then shape into 2cm thick burgers, 6-8 pieces.

Pop the burgers onto another lined baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Divide the roast potatoes between #plates{}.

Serve mini burger patties alongside, topped with a dollop of @ketchup{2%sachets}.

Serve any remaining ketchup alongside for dipping.